  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Life-threatening polymicrobial necrotizing fasciitis of perineum, genitalia, or perianal area.\nMostly bacteria lower GI system -\nB. fragilis\nand\nE. coli\nObliterative endarteritis of subcutaneous arterioles leads to gangrene of overlying skin\n[1]\nMortality - often cited as 20-40%, but up to 80% in some studies\n[2]",
      "subsections": {
        "Risk_Factors": {
          "text": "Diabetes mellitus\n(most common)\nHypertension\nAlcoholism\nAdvanced age\nPara/Quadriplegic\nMales>Females (10:1)\n[1]\n, (likely under-diagnosed in women\n[2]\n)",
