    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Initial event is usually local trauma or extension of a UTI or perianal infection\n[1]\nGangrene develops over 2-7 days\nMarked pain, localized swelling, crepitus, ecchymosis to genital or perineal area.\nFever\nMalodorous purulent drainage\nIn late or severe cases, patient may present in septic shock",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
