    "Management": {
      "text": "Immediate surgery and urology consult for surgical debridement (gangrene can spread at rate of 2-3 cm/hr\n[1]\n)\nAntibiotics\n- Must cover\ngram positive\n,\ngram negative\n, and\nanaerobes\nVancomycin\n+ (\nimipenem\n1gm IV q24hr\nOR\nmeropenem\n500mg-1gm IV q8hr\nOR\npiperacillin-tazobactam\n3.375gm to 4.5gm IV q6h) +/- (\nclindamycin\n600mg-900mg IV q8h\nOR\nmetronidazole\n1gm IV then 500mg IV q8h)\nPiperacillin-Tazobactam\n3.375-4.5g q6hr and\nlinezolid\n600mg q12hr is an alternative regimen\n[3]\nAggressive supportive care, including fluid resuscitation (and\npressors\n, if indicated)",
